<TITLE> Govt forms 7th National Pay Commission </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 31 (bdnews24.com)  The government has constituted the 7th National Pay Commission to review and recommend a revised pay structure of civil servants and pensioners, a senior government official said on Sunday. Former finance secretary M Mustafizur Rahman will head the 13-member commission that has been asked to make recommendations within six months, finance secretary Mohammad Tareque told bdnews24.com. Former caretaker government adviser M Azizul Haque, and former secretaries AK Abdul Mubin and Habibur Rahman will act as fulltime members of the commission. The finance division has issued a notice. Tareque said the commission was formed to remove discrepancies in the salary structures of government employees. It will revise salary structure, time scale, selection grade, increment and other benefits in line with inflation. The first national Pay Commission was formed in 1972. Five further commissions were formed in 1976, 1984, 1989, 1996 and 2005. Finance adviser AB Mirza Azizul Islam in his budget speech on June 9 said: "The existing pay structure of the low-paid government employees is not consistent with the cost of living." bdnews24.
